  "doc_id": "38276",
  "text": "SChLAP1 (second chromosome locus associated with prostate-1) (also called LINC00913) was first characterized by [CITATION_1] , and was shown to promote development of PCa by inhibiting SWI/SNF, a tumorsuppressing protein complex [CITATION_2] . SChLAP1 is expressed in a subset of PCa and is associated with more aggressive disease [CITATION_3] . Mehra et al. demonstrated that high levels of SChLAP1 expression were correlated with increasing GS and tumor stage (P<0.005) and increased time to development of lethal PCa [CITATION_4] . Additionally, quantifying SChLAP1 expression levels has been shown to be useful for predicting PCa metastasis within 10 years (OR 2.45; 95% CI, 1.70-3.53, P<0.0001) [CITATION_5] . Assays utilizing SChLAP1 for PCa screening are not yet commercially available.",
